"{\"uid\": \"nbcnewyork.com-paris-2024-summer-olympics-how-many-medals-does-katie-ledecky-have-5664475\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Katie Ledecky added to her already record-setting number of medals on Saturday, winning gold in the women's 800m freestyle and further cementing her status as of the greatest U.S. Olympians of all-time.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the second gold medal of the Paris Olympics for the 27-year-old Ledecky, who also won the 1500m freestyle.\", \"from\": 204, \"to\": 317, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She earned a bronze in the 400m freestyle and a silver in the women's 4x200m relay.\", \"from\": 318, \"to\": 401, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was that silver medal that put her above any other American woman swimmer ever.\", \"from\": 402, \"to\": 484, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 456, \"end\": 470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"score\": 0.9999999983465386, \"rank\": 8.844587321105153e-10, \"text\": \"American woman\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us break down just how many medals Ledecky now has in her possession (and it remains very likely she will compete in Los Angeles in 2028, so these numbers could still go up).\", \"from\": 486, \"to\": 664, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 607, \"end\": 618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999994660467171, \"rank\": 3.9416260648725095e-07, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Watch NBC 4 free wherever you are  Ledecky now has 14 overall Olympic medals: Nine golds, four silvers and one bronze over four Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 672, \"end\": 675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9810610183542303, \"rank\": 0.018347120557259518, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In her penultimate race for the Paris Olympics, Ledecky broke a tie she had with Americans Dara Torres, Natalie Coughlin and Jenny Thompson.\", \"from\": 809, \"to\": 949, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"for total medals by an American woman.\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 988, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 973, \"end\": 987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"score\": 0.9999999983465386, \"rank\": 8.844587321105153e-10, \"text\": \"American woman\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Watch all the action from the Paris Olympic and Paralympic Games live on Peacock  Only Michael Phelps has more American Olympics medals, with 28 total.\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 1141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1020, \"end\": 1025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999993951941643, \"rank\": 6.048062911221016e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1077, \"end\": 1091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.34291694066619e-57, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2